- When creating/updating queries for mysql, only use queries that are compatible with mariadb
- When creating/updating for mariadb, only use queries that are compatible with mysql
- if a given sql query will run in mysql but not mariadb, or run in mariadb but not mysql, alert me in the chat, using bold text.
- If you see obvious database optimization that would improve query speed, such as additional indexes or materialized views, make the suggestion
- Use the most performant version of the query
- Use inline documentation to document complex queries well
- If creating a new view or stored procedure without my express direction, document said query very thoroughly, add documentation about it in the Readme file, and alert me about it in the chat